1
00:00:03,570 --> 00:00:04,798
<i>You're born,</i>

2
00:00:04,932 --> 00:00:05,954
<i>you live</i>

3
00:00:06,738 --> 00:00:07,811
<i>and you die.</i>

4
00:00:10,141 --> 00:00:11,762
<i>There are not do-overs.</i>

5
00:00:11,882 --> 00:00:15,865
<i>No second chances to make things right
if you frakked them up the first time.</i>

6
00:00:16,577 --> 00:00:18,166
<i>Not in this life anyway.</i>

7
00:00:24,501 --> 00:00:26,135
<i>This is the Battlestar Pegasus</i>

8
00:00:26,255 --> 00:00:28,901
<i>to the ship claiming to be
the Galactica. Please respond.</i>

9
00:00:29,299 --> 00:00:30,227
<i>Pegasus?</i>

10
00:00:30,434 --> 00:00:32,907
How could that be?
The entire fleet was destroyed.

11
00:00:33,598 --> 00:00:34,764
<i>Admiral Cain.</i>

12
00:00:35,094 --> 00:00:37,486
<i>We had no idea
there were other survivors.</i>

13
00:00:37,606 --> 00:00:40,845
<i>On behalf of the officers and the crew
of the Pegasus,</i>

14
00:00:40,965 --> 00:00:43,454
welcome back to the colonial fleet.

15
00:00:43,838 --> 00:00:45,907
<i>What they did to you was wrong.</i>

16
00:00:46,449 --> 00:00:47,308
<i>Evil.</i>

17
00:00:47,428 --> 00:00:48,626
What you need...

18
00:00:48,888 --> 00:00:50,019
is justice.

19
00:00:54,378 --> 00:00:55,477
<i>Frak you.</i>

20
00:00:57,123 --> 00:01:00,220
<i>And she died knowing that her ship
and her crew were safe</i>

21
00:01:01,558 --> 00:01:04,230
and that her mission
had been accomplished.

22
00:01:05,362 --> 00:01:08,764
Nothing was more important to her than
her ship, her crew, and her mission.

23
00:01:11,465 --> 00:01:15,360
<i>And as I take command of Pegasus,
I pledge to uphold those values</i>

24
00:01:16,072 --> 00:01:18,219
<i>that made her such an effective</i>

25
00:01:18,363 --> 00:01:19,406
<i>and heroic leader.</i>

26
00:01:21,150 --> 00:01:24,022
Word of Fisk's murder has
spread out through the entire fleet.

27
00:01:24,142 --> 00:01:26,193
Crew can fall apart
when their commander is killed.

28
00:01:26,313 --> 00:01:28,579
Pegasus lost two in a matter of weeks.

29
00:01:28,703 --> 00:01:30,730
I'm putting Garner in command.

30
00:01:30,905 --> 00:01:33,340
Commander Garner,
two Baseships just jumped in.

31
00:01:33,706 --> 00:01:35,677
Nukes inbound. We're under attack.

32
00:01:36,111 --> 00:01:39,398
We need those FTLs fixed soon.
Or we're dead.

33
00:01:39,629 --> 00:01:41,095
<i>I need to go down there.</i>

34
00:01:44,014 --> 00:01:44,823
<i>Sir,</i>

35
00:01:44,943 --> 00:01:46,124
<i>we've lost Garner.</i>

36
00:01:49,156 --> 00:01:51,688
<i>He sacrificed himself
to save the Pegasus.</i>

37
00:01:52,070 --> 00:01:53,948
<i>Garner was my decision.</i>

38
00:01:54,660 --> 00:01:56,672
<i>His failure's my responsibility.</i>

39
00:01:58,127 --> 00:01:59,988
Congratulations, Commander.

40
00:02:00,236 --> 00:02:01,990
The Pegasus is your command.

41
00:02:04,879 --> 00:02:06,241
<i>Like I said,</i>

42
00:02:06,757 --> 00:02:08,191
<i>you make your choices</i>

43
00:02:08,408 --> 00:02:09,963
<i>and you live with them.</i>

44
00:02:10,541 --> 00:02:12,512
<i>And in the end, you are those choices.</i>

